<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-05-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-05-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="209" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d209">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Hunter</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Adams</persName></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 1397.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi></placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-05-05"><hi rend="italic">May</hi> 5, 1865</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Your despatch of the 14th ultimo, No. 928,
                            together with its accompanying address by the Anti-slavery Society of
                            Glasgow to the late lamented President Abraham Lincoln, has been
                            received. Though Divine Providence <pb facs="0386" n="346" xml:id="pg_346"/> has seen fit to remove from our midst the great
                            man to whom these congratulations are addressed, you may, at a
                            convenient opportunity, inform the society that the present Chief
                            Magistrate highly appreciates this token of their sympathy with the
                            great work which he has been called to complete.</p>
                        <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>W. HUNTER, <hi rend="italic">Acting
                            Secretary.</hi></signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Charles Francis Adams,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>